      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_L6GkTk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Headings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Solitaire vs. Halo: Which Ring Tells Your Story?</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_Xib8CX": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_YdWL8D": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When you’re thinking of popping the question and you’re looking for the perfect Engagement Ring, the design matters just as much as the sparkle. With so many designs and setting options available, it can feel overwhelming at first but you can never go wrong with timeless choices like solitaire and halo settings. While both are timeless, elegant and incredibly popular, they both cater to different styles.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/solitaires\" title=\"Solitaire Diamond\">Solitaires</a> are an elegant and timeless choice for Engagement Rings. They have been representative of a classic Engagement Ring for decades. Halo settings on the other hand are a sparkier version of Solitaire Rings. The name comes from a ring of smaller diamonds set around the center diamond, like a halo. </p><p>But the question remains, which one should you pick? Let's take a look.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_q6yhtd": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Solitaire Setting?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Solitaire Setting?</h2><p>A solitaire setting features a single diamond mounted prominently on a band - no extra stones, no distractions, just pure, unfiltered brilliance. It’s the ultimate minimalist statement and remains one of the most iconic choices for <a href=\"https://lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\">engagement rings</a> across the world.</p>",
            "custom_id": "solitaire"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_tyEcxn": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Why Choose A Solitaire Ring?",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/solitaire.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>Why Choose A Solitaire Ring?</h2><ul><li>Timeless Charm: A solitaire never goes out of style, from your wedding to your 50th anniversary, your lab grown solitaire engagement ring will always stay in style.</li><li>Clean Look: A solitaire ring has a clean minimalistic look with the focus on one diamond.</li><li>Versatility: Solitaire rings pair well with all wedding bands and are easily <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/stackable-rings\" title=\"Stackable Diamond Rings\">stackable</a> with a simple metal band or pave or eternity styles.</li><li>Easy to clean and maintain: Fewer stones mean fewer crevices for dirt to get into, which makes cleaning your ring a breeze.</li></ul>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_P8pj9B": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Solitaire",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>If you're going for a solitaire, consider a round, oval, or emerald cut lab grown diamond with an excellent cut grade for maximum sparkle. The single diamond becomes the star of the show, so it’s ideal if you’re investing in a high-quality lab grown diamond.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mQgmYK": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Halo Setting?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Halo Setting?</h2><p>A halo setting features a center diamond surrounded by a ring, or halo, of smaller diamonds. This setting adds dimension, brilliance, and the illusion of a larger center stone. Halo rings often sparkle from every angle and feel more intricate than solitaires.</p>",
            "custom_id": "halo"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_QUxaWe": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Why Choose A Halo Ring?",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/halo.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>Why Choose A Halo Ring?</h2><ul><li>Extra Sparkle: The surrounding diamonds in a halo setting catch and reflect light, creating a dazzling effect.</li><li>More for less: The halo makes the center stone appear larger, so you can choose a slightly smaller carat and still enjoy a statement look with a lower budget.</li><li>Design Drama: Halo rings often have a vintage charm or glam appeal, perfect if your partner loves a bold or luxurious style.</li><li>Endless Customisation: From double halos to coloured gemstone accents, there’s a halo style for every personality.</li></ul><p></p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_fFUwxm": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "HALO",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Pair a halo setting with a cushion or pear shaped Lab Grown Diamond for a show-stopping look and you’ll be all set for your proposal with a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-halo\" title=\"Lab Grown Halo Engagement Ring\">Lab Grown Halo Engagement Ring</a>.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
