        "rich_text_Y3mqqE": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Budget Considerations",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Budget Considerations</h2><p>If you’re balancing style and budget, both halos and solitaires have their advantages. Solitaires offer timeless elegance and let the diamond speak for itself, often keeping the overall cost focused on a single, high-quality stone. Halos, on the other hand, enhance sparkle and create the appearance of a larger center diamond - allowing you to achieve a bold, luxurious look while staying within a more budget-friendly range. However, the smaller diamonds in a halo ring are more exposed and thus more vulnerable to damage.</p>",
            "custom_id": "budget"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_CXhRet": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Let Love Lead",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Let Love Lead</h2><p>Choosing between a solitaire and a halo setting isn’t just about following trends—it’s about capturing your love story. Ask yourself what feels most true to you: is it quiet, timeless elegance, sparkling and elaborate joy, or perhaps a blend of both?</p><p>At Lucira, we’re here to help you discover the ring that’s as unique as your journey - whether it’s a sleek solitaire or a dazzling halo on your choice of band. With the brilliance of Lab Grown Diamonds and the craftsmanship of our skilled artisans, you can select a piece that tells your story beautifully and responsibly.</p><p>Ready to say yes to the perfect ring? Explore Lucira’s solitaire and halo lab grown diamond engagement rings collection. Because every love story deserves to shine bright and ethically.</p>",
            "custom_id": "love"
          }
        }
      },
